  "description": "Rule 150 — the symmetric XOR-based total rule. Wave interference patterns at high evolution rate (18 Hz) produce machine-like rhythmic staccato. Very short sustain and release means every note is a tight click-and-decay. Projection at 0.2 (narrow window) emphasizes sharp transient harmonics. Envelope routes to FilterCutoff for attack brightness that vanishes quickly — percussive and pointed. Stack with a kick drum. The automaton is marching.",
